author: The Press-Enterprise
title: LOCAL COLLEGES: Cal Baptist teams win swim meet
text:
News Service Reports
Published: Oct. 10, 2015 Updated: 10:47 p.m. The Cal Baptist men’s and women’s swimming and diving teams both took first place at the PCSC Pentathlon on Saturday.
The men finished with a score of 1,131. Josh Hanson won four of five events, including the 100-meter butterfly with a time of 49.38.
The women finished with a score of 650. Ashley Johnson won the 50-meter freestyle with a time of 24.73.
CROSS COUNTRY
UC San Diego Triton Classic: CSUSB won the event with 64 points, Patricia Cortez finished the 6K course in 22:17.73 to finish fourth.
Jessica Steinhoff finished in 14th with a time of 22:58.92, and Laura Aceves took 16th in 23:04.31.
WOMEN’S VOLLEYBALL
CSUSB 3, Cal State East Bay 0: The Coyotes defeated the Pioneers 25-22, 25-16, 25-17 at home.
Malika O'Brien led the Coyotes with 12 kills.
Jayann DeHoog finished with 32 assists and 13 digs.
CBU 3, Chaminade 1: The Lancers (13-3, 6-2 PacWest) defeated the Silverswords (12-4, 5-3) 25-22, 22-25, 25-20, 25-20 at home.
Lauren Hackett led the Lancers with 16 kills, and Jordyn Siko tallied 37 assists.
UCI 3, UCR 0: The Highlanders (6-12, 1-4) fell 25-20, 25-22, 25-21 to the host Anteaters (8-10, 2-4).
Fabiana Rosas finished with 15 kills, and Maddie Hubbell tallied 17 digs.
